=========================================================================================



Uruguay is a small country with a lot of history, unparalleled nature due to its geographic location, a beautiful coastline, really friendly people and a Capital city with many attractions!

This country is located in a privileged location in South America, bordered by the huge territories of Argentina and Brasil, big rivers and the Atlantic Ocean.

With South America's most important summer resorts, Uruguay catches the attention of a lot of people, from the most successful CEOs in the world to the everyday Python coder.

Uruguay is the home of countless soccer and tango legends, but the most important of all, it's the country with one of the highest rate of Python installations per capita due to the simple fact that is the only country in the world where every child has a OLPC XO laptop.

Some important data about Uruguay

Population:  ~ 3,318,535
Area: 176.215 km² (68,037 sq mi)
Language: Spanish
Bordered by: Argentina, Brasil
Capital: Montevideo
Voltaje: 220 V / 50 Hz
International call preffix: +598
Time Zone: GMT/UTC -3 hours
Currency: $ - Uruguayan Peso (UYU)
Documents needed to enter Uruguay: Only valid passport.

